'''Churchianity''' is a pejorative term used by some [[Christian]]s to describe practices of [[Christianity]] that place a large emphasis on the [[institution]]al traditions of the [[church]] (rituals, committees, and programs), rather than on the teachings or [[gospel]]s of [[Jesus]].

